<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by naxy on 04-24-2001 11:32 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Great posts. I think Georgia Gaelicmyst hit it in one.

  [QUOTE]This game should have been designed in such a way that ALL can enjoy all aspects of it. No limiting introduction of items via long spawn times, rare drop rates, etc. Dynamic content is needed, so that if 5 guilds want to take on A single raid simultaneously, all can do it, in their own raid.[/QUOTE]

Meddik, I think that game has been built and I have played it a lot. It is called Diablo/Diablo II. I found that it held my attention about a 1/10th of the time that EQ has. (Agree with most of what you say Meddik, not picking on you.)

Diablo was still a great game, but there is something to this world of Norrath that brings me back. Despite the jerks and stupid stuff that happens. It is primarily the people, but also the fact that Norrath isn't always arranged the way that would suite me the best. Just like RL when you think about it. So when I achieve something, then it is an actuall achivement. When I lost all my "stuff" in Dialbo due to being owerwhelmed and dying and not being able to get it back it was annoying, but not traumatic as it would be if I lost what my 2 year old EQ cleric carries around. A huge emotional difference. Which I think reflects the depths of the games.

I too belive that the game is mostly being played as designed. But with 30k-90k people on at anytime it is virtually impossible to police the whole thing, PnP or no PnP. I also belive you cannot design a game that would be as fun and involving as this, if there were no "real" dangers there. From trains, kill stealers, mobs, lost corpses, etc.

In the end it is "just a game", even though it is easy to forget sometimes. And I belive you will always have some people behaving like jerks when they can hide behind the anonymity EQ provides with virtually no risk of being taken down. But most people I come across are really nice, but then that may be because I am not camping Ragefire.   :)

Verant should have separate servers where only nice people could play.  :p

------------------
Naxy Dent, Cleric and accidental elder of Nature's Way, on Bristlebane

[This message has been edited by naxy (edited 04-24-2001).]</TEXTAREA>
